00:02:05.596 --> 00:02:07.476 A:middle
Creating dynamic notifications

00:02:07.476 --> 00:02:08.916 A:middle
with images and text has been an

00:02:08.916 --> 00:02:10.536 A:middle
option since WatchOS 1.

00:02:10.795 --> 00:02:11.916 A:middle
But if the user missed the

00:02:11.916 --> 00:02:13.416 A:middle
notification when it arrived,

00:02:14.376 --> 00:02:15.666 A:middle
chances were they'd never see it

00:02:15.666 --> 00:02:17.246 A:middle
at all, as the Notification

00:02:17.246 --> 00:02:18.756 A:middle
Center would display the static

00:02:18.816 --> 00:02:19.246 A:middle
version.

00:02:20.056 --> 00:02:22.086 A:middle
This was intentional, as we have

00:02:22.086 --> 00:02:23.136 A:middle
more time to display the

00:02:23.136 --> 00:02:24.546 A:middle
notification when it arrives

00:02:24.576 --> 00:02:25.676 A:middle
than we do when displaying it

00:02:25.676 --> 00:02:26.926 A:middle
from Notification Center.

00:02:28.676 --> 00:02:30.856 A:middle
In WatchOS 5, we'll do our best

00:02:30.856 --> 00:02:32.276 A:middle
to show that beautiful dynamic

00:02:32.276 --> 00:02:34.686 A:middle
notification with no code

00:02:34.686 --> 00:02:36.136 A:middle
changes or recompilation

00:02:36.136 --> 00:02:37.136 A:middle
required on your part.

00:02:38.346 --> 00:02:39.426 A:middle
We worked hard to make this

00:02:39.426 --> 00:02:41.446 A:middle
possible for its own sake but

00:02:41.446 --> 00:02:42.706 A:middle
being able to show dynamic

00:02:42.706 --> 00:02:44.176 A:middle
notifications from Notification

00:02:44.176 --> 00:02:46.086 A:middle
Center also makes possible the

00:02:46.086 --> 00:02:47.456 A:middle
next two features I'm going to

00:02:47.456 --> 00:02:48.076 A:middle
tell you about.

00:02:50.016 --> 00:02:51.676 A:middle
The first of these is grouped

00:02:51.676 --> 00:02:52.576 A:middle
notifications.

00:02:53.446 --> 00:02:55.036 A:middle
You probably already know that

00:02:55.036 --> 00:02:56.656 A:middle
you can have multiple categories

00:02:56.816 --> 00:02:58.016 A:middle
and different notification

00:02:58.016 --> 00:02:59.536 A:middle
interfaces for each one.

00:02:59.536 --> 00:03:01.116 A:middle
And you might already be

00:02:59.536 --> 00:03:01.116 A:middle
And you might already be

00:03:01.116 --> 00:03:02.816 A:middle
specifying a thread ID and the

00:03:02.816 --> 00:03:04.116 A:middle
push notifications that get

00:03:04.116 --> 00:03:05.806 A:middle
forwarded from iOS to the Watch.

00:03:07.576 --> 00:03:09.856 A:middle
In WatchOS 5, this will cause

00:03:09.856 --> 00:03:11.166 A:middle
notifications to be grouped

00:03:11.166 --> 00:03:12.666 A:middle
automatically in Notification

00:03:12.666 --> 00:03:13.806 A:middle
Center as you saw in the

00:03:13.806 --> 00:03:14.456 A:middle
previous slide.

00:03:15.706 --> 00:03:17.906 A:middle
Specifying a category and thread

00:03:17.906 --> 00:03:19.356 A:middle
ID also opens up another

00:03:19.356 --> 00:03:20.086 A:middle
possibility.

00:03:20.606 --> 00:03:23.406 A:middle
Getting the same behavior as the

00:03:23.406 --> 00:03:25.306 A:middle
built-in messages app, where new

00:03:25.306 --> 00:03:26.726 A:middle
notifications with the same

00:03:26.726 --> 00:03:28.046 A:middle
thread ID that come in when the

00:03:28.046 --> 00:03:29.706 A:middle
original one is still on screen

00:03:30.146 --> 00:03:31.586 A:middle
are appended to the existing

00:03:31.586 --> 00:03:32.036 A:middle
interface.

00:03:33.406 --> 00:03:34.776 A:middle
We made this kind of grouping

00:03:34.776 --> 00:03:36.646 A:middle
behavior optional to give you a

00:03:36.646 --> 00:03:37.986 A:middle
chance to handle being called

00:03:37.986 --> 00:03:39.446 A:middle
multiple times for the same

00:03:39.446 --> 00:03:40.556 A:middle
notification interface

00:03:40.556 --> 00:03:40.976 A:middle
controller.

00:03:43.736 --> 00:03:45.466 A:middle
To opt into this behavior,

00:03:45.606 --> 00:03:46.896 A:middle
select your notifications

00:03:46.976 --> 00:03:48.666 A:middle
category in the interface

00:03:48.666 --> 00:03:51.116 A:middle
storyboard for your Watch app.

00:03:51.206 --> 00:03:52.446 A:middle
And check the handle's grouping

00:03:52.446 --> 00:03:54.316 A:middle
box in the attributes inspector.

00:03:55.586 --> 00:03:57.186 A:middle
If the original notification is

00:03:57.186 --> 00:03:58.566 A:middle
on screen when additional

00:03:58.566 --> 00:04:00.306 A:middle
notifications that have a

00:03:58.566 --> 00:04:00.306 A:middle
notifications that have a

00:04:00.306 --> 00:04:01.816 A:middle
matching category and thread ID

00:04:01.816 --> 00:04:03.986 A:middle
arrive, did receive notification

00:04:03.986 --> 00:04:05.296 A:middle
will be called again on the

00:04:05.296 --> 00:04:06.856 A:middle
existing notification interface

00:04:06.856 --> 00:04:07.386 A:middle
controller.

00:04:07.916 --> 00:04:10.066 A:middle
So, you should be prepared to

00:04:10.066 --> 00:04:11.686 A:middle
append content to the existing

00:04:11.686 --> 00:04:12.856 A:middle
notification interface.

00:04:13.236 --> 00:04:14.936 A:middle
Perhaps by adding a blank line

00:04:15.346 --> 00:04:16.696 A:middle
and the new body content to an

00:04:16.696 --> 00:04:17.505 A:middle
existing label.

00:04:17.856 --> 00:04:19.076 A:middle
Or by adding a new row to a

00:04:19.076 --> 00:04:20.245 A:middle
table, as you saw on the

00:04:20.245 --> 00:04:21.125 A:middle
previous example.

00:04:24.486 --> 00:04:25.566 A:middle
And speaking of did receive

00:04:25.566 --> 00:04:27.216 A:middle
notification, its signature has

00:04:27.246 --> 00:04:28.556 A:middle
changed in WatchOS 5.

00:04:29.536 --> 00:04:30.556 A:middle
This version, with the

00:04:30.556 --> 00:04:31.896 A:middle
completion handler has been

00:04:31.896 --> 00:04:35.196 A:middle
deprecated, in favor of this

00:04:35.256 --> 00:04:36.286 A:middle
simplified version.

00:04:37.166 --> 00:04:38.356 A:middle
We did this, so we'd have a

00:04:38.356 --> 00:04:39.616 A:middle
clear boundary for when you're

00:04:39.616 --> 00:04:40.686 A:middle
done processing your

00:04:40.686 --> 00:04:41.676 A:middle
notification data.

00:04:41.676 --> 00:04:43.116 A:middle
And we'd know that everything is

00:04:43.116 --> 00:04:44.326 A:middle
ready to be shown on screen.

00:04:45.366 --> 00:04:47.166 A:middle
We encourage you to do only the

00:04:47.166 --> 00:04:49.126 A:middle
work necessary to display the

00:04:49.126 --> 00:04:51.176 A:middle
notification and to do it as

00:04:51.176 --> 00:04:52.196 A:middle
quickly as possible.

00:04:54.536 --> 00:04:56.516 A:middle
By the way, it's not necessary

00:04:56.516 --> 00:04:57.896 A:middle
for the user to keep their wrist

00:04:57.896 --> 00:04:59.636 A:middle
up to see all the notifications

00:04:59.636 --> 00:05:01.026 A:middle
with the same thread ID as they

00:04:59.636 --> 00:05:01.026 A:middle
with the same thread ID as they

00:05:01.026 --> 00:05:01.556 A:middle
come in.

00:05:02.376 --> 00:05:03.736 A:middle
If you're handling grouping and

00:05:03.736 --> 00:05:04.926 A:middle
the dynamic interface for your

00:05:04.926 --> 00:05:06.596 A:middle
notification category, all the

00:05:06.596 --> 00:05:08.116 A:middle
messages with the same thread ID

00:05:08.116 --> 00:05:09.996 A:middle
will expand to a single platter

00:05:10.146 --> 00:05:11.466 A:middle
when the user taps on the group

00:05:11.466 --> 00:05:12.686 A:middle
and Notification Center.

00:05:12.686 --> 00:05:15.216 A:middle
And if additional messages on

00:05:15.216 --> 00:05:16.646 A:middle
that thread come in, they'll be

00:05:16.646 --> 00:05:18.306 A:middle
appended live is when the long

00:05:18.306 --> 00:05:19.476 A:middle
look was first on screen.

00:05:24.256 --> 00:05:25.366 A:middle
So, here's a big one.

00:05:26.466 --> 00:05:28.406 A:middle
In WatchOS 5, you can now bring

00:05:28.406 --> 00:05:29.776 A:middle
some of your apps' functionality

00:05:29.846 --> 00:05:31.446 A:middle
directly into the notifications

00:05:31.446 --> 00:05:33.356 A:middle
you send by including elements

00:05:33.496 --> 00:05:34.756 A:middle
that let the user interact with

00:05:34.816 --> 00:05:36.306 A:middle
content in the notification

00:05:36.306 --> 00:05:36.746 A:middle
itself.

00:05:38.716 --> 00:05:40.546 A:middle
For example, you could let a

00:05:40.546 --> 00:05:42.136 A:middle
user pay for their ride and rate

00:05:42.136 --> 00:05:44.096 A:middle
their driver, notify a user that

00:05:44.096 --> 00:05:45.566 A:middle
their meter is about to expire,

00:05:45.566 --> 00:05:46.456 A:middle
and let them extend their

00:05:46.456 --> 00:05:48.616 A:middle
parking time, or give a diner an

00:05:48.616 --> 00:05:50.516 A:middle
opportunity to not only confirm

00:05:50.516 --> 00:05:52.086 A:middle
their dinner reservation, but to

00:05:52.086 --> 00:05:53.206 A:middle
let you know they'll be a party

00:05:53.206 --> 00:05:54.356 A:middle
of three instead of four.

00:05:56.456 --> 00:05:57.676 A:middle
So, let's see how all this

00:05:57.676 --> 00:05:58.026 A:middle
works.

00:05:59.116 --> 00:06:00.146 A:middle
If you're creating a new

00:05:59.116 --> 00:06:00.146 A:middle
If you're creating a new

00:06:00.146 --> 00:06:01.186 A:middle
notification interface

00:06:01.186 --> 00:06:02.676 A:middle
controller, a dynamic

00:06:02.676 --> 00:06:04.036 A:middle
interactive interface will be

00:06:04.036 --> 00:06:05.606 A:middle
created for you automatically.

00:06:06.276 --> 00:06:09.326 A:middle
If you already have a dynamic

00:06:09.326 --> 00:06:10.566 A:middle
interface for your notification

00:06:10.566 --> 00:06:12.846 A:middle
category, select the category in

00:06:12.846 --> 00:06:13.876 A:middle
your Watch App's interface

00:06:13.876 --> 00:06:15.536 A:middle
storyboard and check that has

00:06:15.536 --> 00:06:17.446 A:middle
interactive interface box.

00:06:21.656 --> 00:06:23.666 A:middle
In both cases, you'll notice

00:06:23.666 --> 00:06:25.136 A:middle
that the old dynamic interface

00:06:25.136 --> 00:06:26.596 A:middle
is still there, in addition to

00:06:26.596 --> 00:06:27.976 A:middle
the dynamic interactive one.

00:06:28.726 --> 00:06:30.206 A:middle
The dynamic interface will be

00:06:30.206 --> 00:06:31.606 A:middle
shown in WatchOS 5 when the

00:06:31.606 --> 00:06:33.256 A:middle
notification first arrives, and

00:06:33.256 --> 00:06:34.946 A:middle
now in Notification Center as

00:06:34.946 --> 00:06:36.206 A:middle
well, as I mentioned before.

00:06:36.976 --> 00:06:38.906 A:middle
The dynamic interface will be

00:06:38.906 --> 00:06:40.216 A:middle
shown in earlier versions of

00:06:40.216 --> 00:06:41.786 A:middle
WatchOS so, you'll want to keep

00:06:41.786 --> 00:06:42.956 A:middle
that one around for backwards

00:06:42.956 --> 00:06:43.686 A:middle
compatibility.

00:06:44.206 --> 00:06:47.846 A:middle
Once you have a dynamic

00:06:47.846 --> 00:06:49.236 A:middle
interactive interface controller

00:06:49.326 --> 00:06:51.316 A:middle
you can add buttons, switches

00:06:51.316 --> 00:06:52.566 A:middle
and other interactive elements

00:06:52.566 --> 00:06:53.936 A:middle
in the object library, which is

00:06:53.936 --> 00:06:55.286 A:middle
now available at the top of the

00:06:55.286 --> 00:06:56.816 A:middle
screen as a popover menu.

00:06:57.406 --> 00:07:02.006 A:middle
You can even add gesture

00:06:57.406 --> 00:07:02.006 A:middle
You can even add gesture

00:07:02.006 --> 00:07:02.946 A:middle
recognizers with your

00:07:02.946 --> 00:07:04.526 A:middle
notification, though you should

00:07:04.526 --> 00:07:05.666 A:middle
be aware that the system

00:07:05.666 --> 00:07:07.596 A:middle
gestures will take precedence

00:07:07.596 --> 00:07:09.286 A:middle
over any gestures you add in the

00:07:09.286 --> 00:07:09.976 A:middle
same areas.

00:07:16.466 --> 00:07:17.526 A:middle
Once you've designed your

00:07:17.526 --> 00:07:19.326 A:middle
notification interface wire up

00:07:19.326 --> 00:07:20.666 A:middle
the interactive elements to your

00:07:20.666 --> 00:07:21.786 A:middle
code, the way you would any

00:07:21.786 --> 00:07:23.306 A:middle
other interactive element in

00:07:23.306 --> 00:07:24.226 A:middle
your app.

00:07:25.306 --> 00:07:26.426 A:middle
As you can see here, I'm

00:07:26.426 --> 00:07:28.576 A:middle
dragging my IB action for up

00:07:28.576 --> 00:07:30.456 A:middle
button tapped to the button in

00:07:30.456 --> 00:07:31.546 A:middle
my dynamic interactive

00:07:31.546 --> 00:07:32.096 A:middle
interface.

00:07:32.206 --> 00:07:33.346 A:middle
So, the amount of time will

00:07:33.346 --> 00:07:35.136 A:middle
increase by 15 minutes every

00:07:35.136 --> 00:07:39.106 A:middle
time the button is tapped.

00:07:39.106 --> 00:07:40.626 A:middle
And with all this button tapping

00:07:40.856 --> 00:07:42.186 A:middle
you may have already forgotten

00:07:42.186 --> 00:07:43.706 A:middle
that notifications have always

00:07:43.706 --> 00:07:45.036 A:middle
launched your app when tapped.

00:07:46.246 --> 00:07:49.026 A:middle
This is still true for a regular

00:07:49.026 --> 00:07:50.086 A:middle
dynamic and static

00:07:50.376 --> 00:07:51.146 A:middle
notifications.

00:07:51.596 --> 00:07:53.066 A:middle
But, we obviously had to disable

00:07:53.066 --> 00:07:54.476 A:middle
this behavior for dynamic

00:07:54.476 --> 00:07:56.176 A:middle
interactive notifications.

00:07:56.286 --> 00:07:57.236 A:middle
Because we have interactive

00:07:57.236 --> 00:07:57.966 A:middle
elements in them now.

00:07:59.136 --> 00:08:00.316 A:middle
You can still launch your app

00:07:59.136 --> 00:08:00.316 A:middle
You can still launch your app

00:08:00.556 --> 00:08:01.256 A:middle
from an interactive

00:08:01.256 --> 00:08:02.826 A:middle
notification, if you need to.

00:08:02.926 --> 00:08:03.906 A:middle
You just have to do it

00:08:03.906 --> 00:08:05.376 A:middle
explicitly by calling a new

00:08:05.596 --> 00:08:07.546 A:middle
method, performed notification

00:08:07.546 --> 00:08:09.206 A:middle
default action.

00:08:11.416 --> 00:08:13.216 A:middle
Similarly, if you include a

00:08:13.216 --> 00:08:14.646 A:middle
button in your notification

00:08:14.646 --> 00:08:16.126 A:middle
