notification using a standard

00:08:38.186 --> 00:08:38.916 A:middle
action button.

00:08:39.106 --> 00:08:40.535 A:middle
Since action buttons always

00:08:40.576 --> 00:08:41.676 A:middle
dismiss the notification.

00:08:42.246 --> 00:08:44.966 A:middle
Wait, you're probably thinking,

00:08:45.446 --> 00:08:46.616 A:middle
action buttons are shared

00:08:46.616 --> 00:08:47.846 A:middle
between all the notification

00:08:47.846 --> 00:08:48.656 A:middle
interfaces.

00:08:48.656 --> 00:08:49.816 A:middle
And some of those buttons

00:08:49.816 --> 00:08:51.076 A:middle
wouldn't make sense if the

00:08:51.076 --> 00:08:52.196 A:middle
interactive elements weren't

00:08:52.196 --> 00:08:52.526 A:middle
there.

00:08:53.526 --> 00:08:55.916 A:middle
Well, new in WatchOS 5, you can

00:08:55.916 --> 00:08:57.426 A:middle
now adjust the action buttons

00:08:57.426 --> 00:08:58.756 A:middle
that are shown at runtime.

00:08:59.276 --> 00:09:02.316 A:middle
There's a new notification

00:08:59.276 --> 00:09:02.316 A:middle
There's a new notification

00:09:02.436 --> 00:09:03.516 A:middle
actions property on the

00:09:03.516 --> 00:09:04.556 A:middle
notification interface

00:09:04.556 --> 00:09:06.066 A:middle
controller that returns the

00:09:06.066 --> 00:09:07.106 A:middle
array of actions that will be

00:09:07.106 --> 00:09:08.526 A:middle
displayed for the notification.

00:09:09.256 --> 00:09:10.646 A:middle
You can set this property to a

00:09:10.646 --> 00:09:12.756 A:middle
new array of UN notification

00:09:12.866 --> 00:09:14.286 A:middle
action objects in your did

00:09:14.286 --> 00:09:15.636 A:middle
receive notification call back.

00:09:16.436 --> 00:09:17.816 A:middle
which gives you the flexibility

00:09:17.816 --> 00:09:19.606 A:middle
to add or remove buttons to suit

00:09:19.606 --> 00:09:20.836 A:middle
your interactive interface.

00:09:21.526 --> 00:09:25.266 A:middle
And in an upcoming seed, we're

00:09:25.266 --> 00:09:26.426 A:middle
going to allow changes to

00:09:26.426 --> 00:09:28.236 A:middle
actions any time after did

00:09:28.236 --> 00:09:29.676 A:middle
receive notification is called.

00:09:30.326 --> 00:09:30.936 A:middle
Which will give you the

00:09:30.936 --> 00:09:32.646 A:middle
flexibility to change the action

00:09:32.646 --> 00:09:34.376 A:middle
buttons based on how the user

00:09:34.376 --> 00:09:35.776 A:middle
interacts with the elements in

00:09:35.776 --> 00:09:36.916 A:middle
the interactive notification

00:09:36.916 --> 00:09:37.386 A:middle
interface.

00:09:37.986 --> 00:09:42.276 A:middle
So, that's a lot of information

00:09:42.276 --> 00:09:43.986 A:middle
about notifications and the

00:09:43.986 --> 00:09:45.156 A:middle
options for creating them so

00:09:45.156 --> 00:09:45.496 A:middle
far.

00:09:46.106 --> 00:09:48.246 A:middle
But I have two more things to

00:09:48.246 --> 00:09:49.446 A:middle
tell you about before we move

00:09:50.296 --> 00:09:50.366 A:middle
on.

00:09:52.096 --> 00:09:54.336 A:middle
Critical alerts are a new kind

00:09:54.336 --> 00:09:55.606 A:middle
of notification that will cause

00:09:55.606 --> 00:09:57.476 A:middle
a prominent haptic and a sound

00:09:57.476 --> 00:09:59.166 A:middle
to play even when your Watch is

00:09:59.166 --> 00:10:00.596 A:middle
silenced or in do not disturb

00:09:59.166 --> 00:10:00.596 A:middle
silenced or in do not disturb

00:10:00.596 --> 00:10:00.866 A:middle
mode.

00:10:01.606 --> 00:10:02.646 A:middle
And thus, they can be used to

00:10:02.646 --> 00:10:03.896 A:middle
deliver extra urgent

00:10:03.896 --> 00:10:04.606 A:middle
information.

00:10:05.686 --> 00:10:07.336 A:middle
If your Watch app integrates

00:10:07.336 --> 00:10:09.186 A:middle
with a medical device or is used

00:10:09.186 --> 00:10:10.986 A:middle
by emergency responders, this

00:10:11.076 --> 00:10:12.446 A:middle
kind of alert might be for you.

00:10:13.886 --> 00:10:15.716 A:middle
Critical alerts require an app

00:10:15.716 --> 00:10:18.116 A:middle
entitlements and explicit

00:10:18.116 --> 00:10:19.466 A:middle
permission to be granted by the

00:10:19.466 --> 00:10:20.806 A:middle
user separate from regular

00:10:20.806 --> 00:10:21.536 A:middle
notification.

00:10:21.536 --> 00:10:26.166 A:middle
The opposite of a critical alert

00:10:26.166 --> 00:10:27.386 A:middle
is one that can be delivered

00:10:27.446 --> 00:10:27.996 A:middle
quietly.

00:10:28.716 --> 00:10:29.856 A:middle
That is, rather than

00:10:29.856 --> 00:10:31.576 A:middle
interrupting the user with an in

00:10:31.576 --> 00:10:32.776 A:middle
the moment notification that

00:10:32.776 --> 00:10:34.796 A:middle
takes over the screen, you can

00:10:34.796 --> 00:10:36.486 A:middle
now choose to send notifications

00:10:36.586 --> 00:10:38.376 A:middle
directly to Notification Center.

00:10:39.256 --> 00:10:40.656 A:middle
You'll notice that no indicator

00:10:40.656 --> 00:10:42.816 A:middle
will appear unless a prominently

00:10:42.816 --> 00:10:44.386 A:middle
delivered notification is also

00:10:44.386 --> 00:10:45.476 A:middle
in Notification Center.

00:10:45.986 --> 00:10:47.936 A:middle
But the swipe from the top of

00:10:47.936 --> 00:10:49.316 A:middle
the screen will still reveal the

00:10:49.316 --> 00:10:50.866 A:middle
quietly delivered notification.

00:10:56.336 --> 00:10:57.316 A:middle
If you choose to deliver

00:10:57.316 --> 00:10:59.296 A:middle
notifications quietly in your

00:10:59.296 --> 00:11:01.636 A:middle
app, you don't have to prompt

00:10:59.296 --> 00:11:01.636 A:middle
app, you don't have to prompt

00:11:01.636 --> 00:11:03.506 A:middle
the user to allow notifications

00:11:03.626 --> 00:11:05.016 A:middle
when the app is first launched.

00:11:05.976 --> 00:11:07.286 A:middle
Instead, you can request

00:11:07.426 --> 00:11:08.516 A:middle
provisional permission.

00:11:09.386 --> 00:11:10.856 A:middle
This gives the user a chance to

00:11:10.856 --> 00:11:12.556 A:middle
see what kinds of notifications

00:11:12.556 --> 00:11:14.306 A:middle
your app sends before having to

00:11:14.306 --> 00:11:15.826 A:middle
decide whether they want to see

00:11:15.976 --> 00:11:19.426 A:middle
them as they arrive.

00:11:19.426 --> 00:11:21.156 A:middle
Whichever option you choose as a

00:11:21.156 --> 00:11:23.146 A:middle
developer, the user still has

00:11:23.146 --> 00:11:24.656 A:middle
ultimate control over how they

00:11:24.656 --> 00:11:26.106 A:middle
receive your notifications.

00:11:26.866 --> 00:11:28.026 A:middle
They can choose to deliver

00:11:28.026 --> 00:11:30.256 A:middle
notifications quietly by swiping

00:11:30.256 --> 00:11:31.716 A:middle
left from a notification in

00:11:31.716 --> 00:11:33.546 A:middle
Notification Center or change

00:11:33.546 --> 00:11:36.156 A:middle
their notification preferences

00:11:36.376 --> 00:11:36.976 A:middle
in settings.

00:11:41.116 --> 00:11:43.906 A:middle
To sum up, notifications are now

00:11:43.906 --> 00:11:44.616 A:middle
more dynamic.

00:11:45.246 --> 00:11:46.516 A:middle
Users will see your dynamic

00:11:46.516 --> 00:11:48.276 A:middle
interface from Notification

00:11:48.276 --> 00:11:50.076 A:middle
Center in addition to when the

00:11:50.076 --> 00:11:51.276 A:middle
notification first arrives.

00:11:52.366 --> 00:11:53.726 A:middle
We're also offering grouping by

00:11:53.726 --> 00:11:55.656 A:middle
thread ID for the first time on

00:11:55.656 --> 00:11:56.046 A:middle
the Watch.

00:11:56.046 --> 00:11:58.796 A:middle
So, you can design notifications

00:11:58.796 --> 00:12:00.066 A:middle
that behave like the ones like

00:11:58.796 --> 00:12:00.066 A:middle
that behave like the ones like

00:12:00.066 --> 00:12:01.786 A:middle
the built-in messages app.

00:12:02.556 --> 00:12:04.086 A:middle
You can now bring more of your

00:12:04.176 --> 00:12:05.946 A:middle
app experience directly into the

00:12:05.946 --> 00:12:07.746 A:middle
notification your app delivers

00:12:07.956 --> 00:12:09.606 A:middle
with interactive controls and

00:12:09.686 --> 00:12:10.646 A:middle
action buttons that can be

00:12:10.646 --> 00:12:11.566 A:middle
defined at runtime.

00:12:12.796 --> 00:12:14.356 A:middle
And you can also choose to

00:12:14.356 --> 00:12:15.746 A:middle
deliver notifications with the

00:12:15.746 --> 00:12:17.346 A:middle
appropriate level of urgency.

00:12:18.636 --> 00:12:19.426 A:middle
To learn more about

00:12:19.426 --> 00:12:23.256 A:middle
notifications you can attend one

00:12:23.256 --> 00:12:24.546 A:middle
of these sessions.

00:12:24.986 --> 00:12:26.906 A:middle
I highly recommend Designing

00:12:26.906 --> 00:12:28.566 A:middle
Notifications, that will give

00:12:28.566 --> 00:12:29.746 A:middle
you some great tips for how to

00:12:30.306 --> 00:12:32.546 A:middle
design effective interactive

00:12:32.646 --> 00:12:33.406 A:middle
notifications.

00:12:36.586 --> 00:12:38.766 A:middle
Okay, now that we have your

00:12:38.766 --> 00:12:40.286 A:middle
user's attention with

00:12:40.286 --> 00:12:42.326 A:middle
notifications, let's turn our

00:12:42.326 --> 00:12:44.086 A:middle
attention to the features we're

00:12:44.086 --> 00:12:45.546 A:middle
adding to make your Watch apps

00:12:45.546 --> 00:12:46.136 A:middle
more awesome.

00:12:47.326 --> 00:12:48.996 A:middle
The first has to do with local

00:12:48.996 --> 00:12:49.756 A:middle
audio playback.

00:12:51.716 --> 00:12:53.346 A:middle
Some of you have already made

00:12:53.346 --> 00:12:55.116 A:middle
forays into audio playback on

00:12:55.116 --> 00:12:56.726 A:middle
the Watch by taking advantage of

00:12:56.726 --> 00:12:58.216 A:middle
URL session for downloading

00:12:58.216 --> 00:12:59.116 A:middle
files to the Watch.

00:12:59.576 --> 00:13:01.526 A:middle
And WK audio file queue player

00:12:59.576 --> 00:13:01.526 A:middle
And WK audio file queue player

00:13:01.526 --> 00:13:02.076 A:middle
to play them.

00:13:03.416 --> 00:13:05.216 A:middle
With WatchOS 5, we're going to

00:13:05.216 --> 00:13:06.776 A:middle
make developing audio apps for

00:13:06.776 --> 00:13:08.626 A:middle
the Watch even easier, and the

00:13:08.626 --> 00:13:10.196 A:middle
resulting experiences more

00:13:10.196 --> 00:13:10.706 A:middle
delightful.

00:13:13.036 --> 00:13:15.046 A:middle
In WatchOS 5, we're offering a

00:13:15.046 --> 00:13:16.866 A:middle
new background mode for playing

00:13:16.866 --> 00:13:17.906 A:middle
local audio files.

00:13:17.906 --> 00:13:20.106 A:middle
So, you can now focus on your

00:13:20.196 --> 00:13:22.396 A:middle
app's main purpose, audio,

00:13:22.906 --> 00:13:24.326 A:middle
rather than trying to figure out

00:13:24.326 --> 00:13:26.206 A:middle
how to build something else like

00:13:26.206 --> 00:13:28.236 A:middle
a workout app just to be able to

00:13:28.286 --> 00:13:28.836 A:middle
play audio.

00:13:30.516 --> 00:13:34.876 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:13:35.376 --> 00:13:37.396 A:middle
We also exposed AVAudio player

00:13:37.396 --> 00:13:39.276 A:middle
and AVAudioEngine directly,

00:13:39.586 --> 00:13:40.966 A:middle
which means you can use the same

00:13:40.966 --> 00:13:42.126 A:middle
methods and properties you're

00:13:42.186 --> 00:13:43.716 A:middle
already familiar with if you've

00:13:43.716 --> 00:13:45.556 A:middle
been building iOS apps that play

00:13:45.556 --> 00:13:45.956 A:middle
audio.

